</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> &quot;Joseph N. Hall&quot; &lt;remid0d...@gmail.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-08-04T01:31:00 </POSTDATE>
My quest to play and ascend the lamest class possible seems to settle
on the healer (at least an archaeologist can use a dwarvish mattock).

I can play them to 10-12th level fairly reliably but without some kind
of providence I usually get them killed off around that time. Lately
I've had a stingy RNG that has given me a magic lamp about every third
game, no gratuitous WoWs, no wands of poly, no coaligned altar in
Minetown, a shortage of scummable altars in general, rarely any decent
armor, and even weirdly bad combinations of shops. A couple of games
ago I didn't find a store that sold scrolls until around DL 15 - so I
couldn't even identify &quot;identify&quot; - or any other scroll - without
risking amnesia. That was really, really miserable. Being a mostly
illiterate healer is exasperating.

Playing a healer is enjoyable to me because it's challenging, but at
the same time it's a pretty grim slog, because unless you catch a
break, everything's the hard way. You're weak, the armor/spellcasting
balance is tricky and unfavorable, the offering weapons are not great
(except for Magicbane) and weapons in general suck, and so on.  It's
kind of depressing that except for Magicbane, none of the offering
weapons can be used beyond basic skill. Ranged attacks? You're stuck
with daggers - which would be okay, except that finding a decent stack
of elven daggers takes time, and you can throw a max of 2/turn. (Can't
a doctor take up archery as a hobby?!?)

I don't mess with protection racket unless I find good spellcasting
armor right away, in which case I creep along behind my pet down to
Minetown as quickly as possible, casting the occasional healing spell
on him as necessary.

I hate seeing that useless 'a' next to &quot;knife&quot; in #enhance, so I
usually start with bare hands until I have a dagger.

Anyway, I am curious to hear what other people do with healers. Are
they just annoying to play? I guess I like them because they're so
lame.
</POST>
