Artifacts resist cursing, and more than -20 AC is unnecessary.

Fear is the mind-killer.  Keep holy water handy and rebless the Staff
anytime it becomes uncursed, and you'll never have a problem.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt;   The staff also turns to junk from Gehennom on as more and more
&gt; monsters are level-drain resistant.
">

Only the following monsters are level-drain resistant:

all undead, all demons, all werefoo, and Death.

Undead and demons respect Elbereth, and as such it doesn't matter how
long it takes you to kill them by beating them to death with a +7 staff.
You can also just use Elbereth to go around them, as they'll start
running away and leave you space to move.

Werefoo are not worth mentioning, leaving Death the only problem.

Far more monsters in Gehennom are _not_ level-drain resistant, and the
Staff is a murderous death machine against those.  Wield it and win.

