Well... that's a tricky one.  Many of the most effective strategies
involve removing any interaction with large portions of the game.  This
reduces any 'fun' that might be gained during those portions, since
you're not actually playing them, you're just passing them by.

But certainly parts of the game (the early- and mid-game, for example)
are definitely still fun, even if you are using the &quot;most effective&quot;
strategies available -- and as such, you most certainly can &quot;play for
fun _and_ to win&quot;.

