The Healer has only one Weapon his pet. You need to use it.
You should play the protection racket in Pacifist mode a few times
till you can reach minetown intact without killing anything.
You will learn how to use your pet and patience along the way.

Remember playing recklessly and then dying is not a lot of fun.
Surviving is.

Disclaimer: I have not ascended a Healer, but my strategy is now
common to all games.

The strategy I use is to complete the Sokoban with the help of pets.
Till this time don't waste time other than exploring and buying any
useful tools or armor from the shops. Don't try to id, or sac or do
anything that might waste time.

Try not to kill anything that your pet can. That leaves floating eyes
and the giant mimics in the top floor of Sokoban. As healer it would
be better to zap the mimic with sleep and your pet with healing.

At the end of Sokoban you should be about 6XL. Before Sokoban
you should be at least 3XL, depending on your circumstances.
I generally gain one XL every three levels.

With Stethoscope and healing spells and stone to flesh you should
have a large number of pets. Keep the ones that you can enlarge
close.

Then return while credit cloning and price-iding all shops found, and
proceed to the mines. You should have enough gold for the minetown
priest, in most cases.

After this it becomes fairly straight forward. You will have found a
unicorn horn by this time use it as your weapon, enhancing it to
Skilled. You should never become expert in a weapon or spell unless
you are getting any added benefit. 1 point of extra damage is useless,
compared to the 3 levels of XL. So become expert only in darts.

Incidentally, the staff is good only till Liches start appearing. But
till
that time you should have your luck maximized, and you can get
long sword unrestricted by sacrifice, so wielding a long sword
(possibly
an artifact) is not a bad option. While throwing expert blessed +7
poisoned darts provides a very quick kill. You could as well be
empty handed.

regards,
